Subject: [PATCH] Preserve pre-c4d35e0 behavior for clang-tidy aspect

Upstream commit c4d35e0 introduced two behavioral changes that don't fit
this project's setup. This patch reverts both:

1. Header files are now linted by default (the aspect treats every public
   header as a main translation unit). For this repository that would
   require fixing a large number of pre-existing IWYU and enum-size
   findings that have never been visible before. Gate the new behavior
   behind the explicit `clang-tidy-headers` tag so header linting stays
   off by default and we can opt-in per-target later.

2. The aspect now injects one `-isystem` flag per entry in
   `cc_toolchain.built_in_include_directories`. For this project's
   GCC-based toolchain those directories include
   `/usr/lib/gcc/<triple>/<ver>`, which Clang normally discovers on its
   own via GCC install-dir auto-detection. Forcing the directory through
   `-isystem` instead bypasses that logic and breaks `include_next`
   lookups, producing errors such as:

     /usr/include/c++/14/cstdlib:79:15: error: 'stdlib.h' file not found
        79 | #include_next <stdlib.h>

   Drop the extra `-isystem` injection so Clang's own auto-detection
   keeps working for our system GCC toolchain.

---
 clang_tidy/clang_tidy.bzl | 5 ++---
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/clang_tidy/clang_tidy.bzl b/clang_tidy/clang_tidy.bzl
--- a/clang_tidy/clang_tidy.bzl
+++ b/clang_tidy/clang_tidy.bzl
@@ -219,9 +219,8 @@ def _clang_tidy_aspect_impl(target, ctx):
     cc_toolchain = find_cpp_toolchain(ctx)
     c_flags = safe_flags(toolchain_flags(ctx, cc_toolchain, ACTION_NAMES.c_compile) + rule_flags) + ["-xc"]
     cxx_flags = safe_flags(toolchain_flags(ctx, cc_toolchain, ACTION_NAMES.cpp_compile) + rule_flags) + ["-xc++"]
-    builtin_flags = builtin_include_flags(cc_toolchain)
 
-    include_headers = "no-clang-tidy-headers" not in ctx.rule.attr.tags
+    include_headers = "clang-tidy-headers" in ctx.rule.attr.tags
     srcs = rule_sources(ctx.rule.attr, include_headers)
 
     outputs = [
@@ -233,7 +232,7 @@ def _clang_tidy_aspect_impl(target, ctx):
             resource_dir,
             additional_deps,
             config,
-            (c_flags if is_c_translation_unit(src, ctx.rule.attr.tags) else cxx_flags) + builtin_flags,
+            c_flags if is_c_translation_unit(src, ctx.rule.attr.tags) else cxx_flags,
             src,
             target.label.name,
             additional_files,
